                            <comment id="16368693" author="ambroff" created="Sun, 18 Feb 2018 22:43:20 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Submitted a PR for the patch we deployed internally. It&apos;s not perfect though since the logger name does change. This wasn&apos;t important for us, but I&apos;m not sure whether this matters to you guys.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="16368701" author="ambroff" created="Sun, 18 Feb 2018 23:14:27 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;The logger name doesn&apos;t change for anything written from kafka.log.OffsetIndex, since the companion object overrides loggerName. However, messages logged from methods in kafka.log.AbstractIndex&lt;span class=&quot;error&quot;&gt;&amp;#91;K, V&amp;#93;&lt;/span&gt; now have the logger name &quot;kafka.log.AbstractIndex$&quot;, where before they would be the class name of object (kafka.log.OffsetIndex).&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
